# 📖 Data Dictionary

This document describes the variables used in the Formula 1 Driver Performance Intelligence project.

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| Driver | Text | Name of the Formula 1 driver |
| Nationality | Text | Driver's country of origin |
| Seasons | Integer | Number of Formula 1 seasons participated |
| Championships | Integer | Total World Championships won |
| Race_Entries | Integer | Total race entries |
| Race_Starts | Integer | Total race starts |
| Pole_Positions | Integer | Total pole positions achieved |
| Race_Wins | Integer | Total race victories |
| Podiums | Integer | Total podium finishes |
| Fastest_Laps | Integer | Total fastest laps recorded |
| Points | Float | Career championship points |
| Active | Boolean | Indicates whether the driver is currently active |
| Championship_Years | Text | Years in which championships were won |
| Decade | Integer | Career decade classification |
| Pole_Rate | Float | Pole positions per race entry |
| Start_Rate | Float | Race starts per race entry |
| Win_Rate | Float | Race wins per race entry |
| Podium_Rate | Float | Podium finishes per race entry |
| FastLap_Rate | Float | Fastest laps per race entry |
| Points_Per_Entry | Float | Average points earned per race entry |
| Years_Active | Integer | Total years active in Formula 1 |
| Champion | Boolean | Target variable indicating championship status |
